#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12691
msgid "The PPP connection"
msgstr "La connexion PPP"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12692
msgid "You need to configure the PPP connection first as described before (see <xref linkend=\"_the_ppp_connection_with_pppconfig\"/>).  Then, add the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file entry for the primary PPP device <literal>ppp0</literal> as the following."
msgstr "Vous devrez d'abord configurer la connexion PPP comme décrit précédemment (voir <xref linkend=\"_the_ppp_connection_with_pppconfig\"/>). Ensuite, ajoutez dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» une entrée pour le périphérique PPP primaire <literal>ppp0</literal> comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12693
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"iface ppp0 inet ppp\n"
" provider &lt;isp_name&gt;"
msgstr ""
"iface ppp0 inet ppp\n"
" provider &lt;nom_fai&gt;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12697
msgid "The alternative PPP connection"
msgstr "La connexion alternative PPP"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12698
msgid "You need to configure the alternative PPP connection with <literal>wvdial</literal> first as described before (see <xref linkend=\"_the_alternative_ppp_connection_with_wvdialconf\"/>).  Then, add the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file entry for the primary PPP device <literal>ppp0</literal> as the following."
msgstr "Vous devrez d'abord configurer la connexion PPP alternative avec <literal>wvdial</literal> comme décrit précédemment (voir <xref linkend=\"_the_alternative_ppp_connection_with_wvdialconf\"/>). Ajoutez ensuite dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» une entrée pour le périphérique primaire PPP <literal>ppp0</literal> comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12699
#, no-wrap
msgid "iface ppp0 inet wvdial"
msgstr "iface ppp0 inet wvdial"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12702
msgid "The PPPoE connection"
msgstr "La connexion PPPoE"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12703
msgid "For PC connected directly to the WAN served by the PPPoE, you need to configure system with the PPPoE connection as described before (see <xref linkend=\"_the_pppoe_connection_with_pppoeconf\"/>).  Then, add the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" file entry for the primary PPPoE device <literal>eth0</literal> as the following."
msgstr "Pour le PC directement connecté au WAN et utilisant PPPoE, vous devez configurer votre système pour une connexion PPPoE comme cela a été décrit précédemment (voir <xref linkend=\"_the_pppoe_connection_with_pppoeconf\"/>). Ajoutez ensuite dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» une entrée pour le premier périphérique PPPoE <literal>eth0</literal> comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12704
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet manual\n"
" pre-up /sbin/ifconfig eth0 up\n"
" up ifup ppp0=dsl\n"
" down ifdown ppp0=dsl\n"
" post-down /sbin/ifconfig eth0 down\n"
"# The following is used internally only\n"
"iface dsl inet ppp\n"
" provider dsl-provider"
msgstr ""
"allow-hotplug eth0\n"
"iface eth0 inet manual\n"
" pre-up /sbin/ifconfig eth0 up\n"
" up ifup ppp0=dsl\n"
" down ifdown ppp0=dsl\n"
" post-down /sbin/ifconfig eth0 down\n"
"# Ce qui suit est utilisé uniquement de manière interne\n"
"iface dsl inet ppp\n"
" provider fournisseur-internet"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12715
msgid "The network configuration state of ifupdown"
msgstr "État de configuration réseau de ifupdown"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12716
msgid "The \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file stores the <emphasis role=\"strong\">intended</emphasis> network configuration states for all the currently active network interfaces managed by the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package are listed. Unfortunately, even if the <literal>ifupdown</literal> system fails to bring up the interface as intended, the \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file lists it active."
msgstr "Le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>&nbsp;» enregistre l'état <emphasis role=\"strong\">désiré</emphasis> de la connexion réseau pour toutes les interfaces réseau actuellement actives et gérées par le paquet <literal>ifupdown</literal>. Malheureusement, même si le système <literal>ifupdown</literal> échoue dans l'activation de l'interface comme désiré, le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>&nbsp;» l'affichera comme active."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12717
msgid "Unless the output of the <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) command for an interface does not have a line like following example, it can not be used as a part of <ulink url=\"&ipvenetwork;\">IPV4 network</ulink>."
msgstr "Si la sortie de la commande <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) d'une interface n'a pas de ligne telle que la suivante, elle ne peut pas être utilisée en tant qu'élément d'un <ulink url=\"&ipvenetwork;\">réseau IPV4</ulink>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12718
#, no-wrap
msgid "  inet addr:192.168.11.2  Bcast:192.168.11.255  Mask:255.255.255.0"
msgstr "  inet addr:192.168.11.2  Bcast:192.168.11.255  Mask:255.255.255.0"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12720
msgid "For the Ethernet device connected to the PPPoE, the output of the <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) command lacks a line which looks like above example."
msgstr "Pour un périphérique ethernet connecté en PPPoE, la sortie de la commande <literal>ifconfig</literal>(8) ne produit pas de ligne semblable à celle de l'exemple ci-dessus."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12724
msgid "The basic network reconfiguration"
msgstr "Configuration réseau de base"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12725
msgid "When you try to reconfigure the interface, e.g. <literal>eth0</literal>, you must disable it first with the \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0</literal></emphasis>\" command.  This removes the entry of <literal>eth0</literal> from the \"<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>\" file. (This may result in some error message if <literal>eth0</literal> is not active or it is configured improperly previously.  So far, it seems to be safe to do this for the simple single user work station at any time.)"
msgstr "Lorsque vous tentez de reconfigurer une interface, par exemple <literal>eth0</literal>, vous devez d'abord la désactiver par la commande «&nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0</literal></emphasis>&nbsp;». Ceci supprime l'entrée <literal>eth0</literal> du fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/run/ifstate</literal>&nbsp;». (Ceci peut donner quelques messages d'erreur si <literal>eth0</literal> n'est pas active ou a mal été configurée auparavant. Jusqu'à présent, il semble qu'il soit sûr de le faire n'importe quand sur une simple station de travail n'ayant qu'un seul utilisateur)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12726
msgid "You are now free to rewrite the \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" contents as needed to reconfigure the network interface, <literal>eth0</literal>."
msgstr "Vous pouvez maintenant  réécrire le contenu du fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» selon vos besoins pour reconfigurer l'interface réseau <literal>eth0</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12727
msgid "Then, you can reactivate <literal>eth0</literal> with the \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>\" command."
msgstr "Ensuite, vous pourrez réactiver <literal>eth0</literal> avec la commande &nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12729
msgid "You can (re)initialize the network interface simply by \"<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0;sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>\"."
msgstr "Vous pouvez (ré)initialiser l'interface réseau simplement par «&nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\"><literal>sudo ifdown eth0;sudo ifup eth0</literal></emphasis>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12733
msgid "The ifupdown-extra package"
msgstr "La paquet ifupdown-extra"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12734
msgid "The <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> package provides easy network connection tests for use with the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> fournit des tests de connexion au réseau facile à utiliser avec le paquet <literal>ifupdown</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12738
msgid "The <literal>network-test</literal>(1) command can be used from the shell."
msgstr "La commande <literal>network-test</literal>(1) peut être utilisée depuis l'interpréteur de commandes."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12743
msgid "The automatic scripts are run for each <literal>ifup</literal> command execution."
msgstr "Les scripts automatiques sont lancés pour chaque exécution de la commande <literal>ifup</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12747
msgid "The <literal>network-test</literal> command frees you from the execution of cumbersome low level commands to analyze the network problem."
msgstr "La commande <literal>network-test</literal> vous libère de l'exécution d'ennuyeuses commandes de bas niveau pour analyser les problèmes du réseau."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12748
msgid "The automatic scripts are installed in \"<literal>/etc/network/*/</literal>\" and performs the following."
msgstr "Les scripts automatiques sont installés dans «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/*/</literal>&nbsp;» et effectuent ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12752
msgid "Check the network cable connection"
msgstr "vérifier la connexion du câble réseau"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12757
msgid "Check duplicate use of IP address"
msgstr "vérifier l'utilisation d'une adresse IP dupliquée"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12762
msgid "Setup system's static routes based on the \"<literal>/etc/network/routes</literal>\" definition"
msgstr "définir les routes statiques du système basées sur la définition de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/routes</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12767
msgid "Check if network gateway is reachable"
msgstr "vérifier si la passerelle réseau peut être atteinte"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12772
msgid "Record results in the \"<literal>/var/log/syslog</literal>\" file"
msgstr "enregistrer les résultats dans le fichier «&nbsp;<literal>/var/log/syslog</literal>&nbsp;»"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12776
msgid "This syslog record is quite useful for administration of the network problem on the remote system."
msgstr "L'enregistrement dans syslog est assez utile pour l'administration des problèmes de réseau sur un système distant."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12778
msgid "The automatic behavior of the <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> package is configurable with the \"<literal>/etc/default/network-test</literal>\". Some of these automatic checks slow down the system boot-up a little bit since it takes some time to listen for <ulink url=\"&arp;\">ARP</ulink> replies."
msgstr "Le comportement automatique du paquet <literal>ifupdown-extra</literal> est configurable par «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/default/network-test</literal>&nbsp;» Certaines de ces vérifications automatiques ralentissent un peu le démarrage du système car elle prennent un certain temps à l'écoute des réponses <ulink url=\"&arp;\">ARP</ulink>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12783
msgid "The advanced network configuration with ifupdown (legacy)"
msgstr "Configuration réseau avancée avec ifupdown (legacy)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12784
msgid "The functionality of the <literal>ifupdown</literal> package can be improved beyond what was described in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/> with the advanced knowledge."
msgstr "Les fonctionnalités du paquet <literal>ifupdown</literal> peuvent être améliorées au-delà de ce qui est décrit dans <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/> avec des connaissances avancées."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12785
msgid "The functionalities described here are completely optional.  I, being lazy and minimalist, rarely bother to use these."
msgstr "Les fonctionnalités décrites ici sont entièrement optionnelles. Étant paresseux et minimaliste, je me suis rarement ennuyé à les utiliser."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12787
msgid "If you could not set up network connection by information in <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/>, you make situation worse by using information below."
msgstr "Si vous n'arrivez pas à établir une connexion réseau à l'aide des informations dans <xref linkend=\"_the_basic_network_configuration_with_ifupdown_legacy\"/>, vous ne ferez qu'empirer la situation en utilisant les informations qui suivent&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12790
msgid "The ifplugd package"
msgstr "La paquet ifplugd"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12791
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "The <literal>ifplugd</literal> package is older automatic network configuration tool which can manage only Ethernet connections. This solves unplugged/replugged Ethernet cable issues for mobile PC etc.  If you have <ulink url=\"&networkmanager;\">NetworkManager</ulink> or <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_automatic_network_configuration\"/>) installed, you do not need this package."
msgid "The <literal>ifplugd</literal> package is older automatic network configuration tool which can manage only Ethernet connections. This solves unplugged/replugged Ethernet cable issues for mobile PC etc.  If you have <ulink url=\"&networkmanager;\">NetworkManager</ulink> or <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_the_modern_network_configuration_for_desktop\"/>) installed, you do not need this package."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>ifplugd</literal> est le plus ancien outil de configuration automatique du réseau, il ne peut gérer que les connexion ethernet. Ceci permet de régler le problème des connexions et déconnexions des câbles ethernet avec les PC mobiles, etc. Si vous avez installé <ulink url=\"&networkmanager;\">NetworkManager</ulink> ou <ulink url=\"&wicd;\">Wicd</ulink> (voir <xref linkend=\"_automatic_network_configuration\"/>), vous n'avez pas besoin de ce paquet."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12792
msgid "This package runs <ulink url=\"&daemon;\">daemon</ulink> and replaces <emphasis role=\"strong\">auto</emphasis> or <emphasis role=\"strong\">allow-hotplug</emphasis> functionalities (see <xref linkend=\"list-of-stanzas-in-eni\"/>) and starts interfaces upon their connection to the network."
msgstr "Ce paquet fait tourner un <ulink url=\"&daemon;\">démon</ulink> qui remplace les fonctionnalités <emphasis role=\"strong\">auto</emphasis> ou <emphasis role=\"strong\">allow-hotplug</emphasis> (voir <xref linkend=\"list-of-stanzas-in-eni\"/>) et qui  active les interfaces lors de leur connexion au réseau."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12793
msgid "Here is how to use the <literal>ifplugd</literal> package for the internal Ethernet port, e.g. <literal>eth0</literal>."
msgstr "Voici comment utiliser le paquet <literal>ifplugd</literal> pour le port ethernet interne, par exemple, <literal>eth0</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12797
msgid "Remove stanza in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\": \"<literal>auto eth0</literal>\" or \"<literal>allow-hotplug eth0</literal>\"."
msgstr "Supprimez l'entrée «&nbsp;<literal>auto eth0</literal>&nbsp;» ou «&nbsp;<literal>allow-hotplug eth0</literal>&nbsp;» de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;»"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12802
msgid "Keep stanza in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\": \"<literal>iface eth0 inet …</literal>\" and \"<literal>mapping …</literal>\"."
msgstr "Conservez les entrées «&nbsp;<literal>iface eth0 inet …</literal>&nbsp;» et «&nbsp;<literal>mapping …</literal>&nbsp;» de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» "

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12807
msgid "Install the <literal>ifplugd</literal> package."
msgstr "Installez le paquet <literal>ifplugd</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12812
msgid "Run \"<literal>sudo dpkg-reconfigure ifplugd</literal>\"."
msgstr "Lancez «&nbsp;<literal>sudo dpkg-reconfigure ifplugd</literal>&nbsp;»"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12817
msgid "Put <literal>eth0</literal> as the \"static interfaces to be watched by ifplugd\"."
msgstr "Mettez <literal>eth0</literal> comme interface «&nbsp;statique devant être surveillée par ifplugd&nbsp;»."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12821
msgid "Now, the network reconfiguration works as you desire."
msgstr "Le réseau fonctionne maintenant comme vous le désirez."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12825
msgid "Upon power-on or upon hardware discovery, the interface is not brought up by itself."
msgstr "Lors de la mise sous tension ou lors de la découverte du matériel, l'interface est activée d'elle-même."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12830
msgid "Quick boot process without the long DHCP timeout."
msgstr "Processus de démarrage rapide sans le long délai de dépassement de temps de DHCP."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12835
msgid "No funny activated interface without proper IPv4 address (see <xref linkend=\"_the_network_configuration_state_of_ifupdown\"/>)."
msgstr "Pas d'interface bizarre activée sans une adresse IPV4 correcte (voir <xref linkend=\"_the_network_configuration_state_of_ifupdown\"/>)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12842
msgid "Upon finding the Ethernet cable, the interface is brought up."
msgstr "L'interface est activée lors de la découverte du câble ethernet."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12847
msgid "Upon some time after unplugging the Ethernet cable, the interface is brought down automatically."
msgstr "L'interface est désactivée quelque temps après que le câble éthernet ait été débranché."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12852
msgid "Upon plugging in another Ethernet cable, the interface is brought up under the new network environment."
msgstr "L'interface est activée dans le nouvel environnement de réseau lors de la connexion d'un autre câble ethernet."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12857
msgid "The arguments for the <literal>ifplugd</literal>(8) command can set its behaviors such as the delay for reconfiguring interfaces."
msgstr "Les paramètres de la commande <literal>ifplugd</literal>(8) peuvent définir son comportement tel que le délai de reconfiguration des interfaces."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12861
msgid "The ifmetric package"
msgstr "Le paquet ifmetric"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12862
msgid "The <literal>ifmeric</literal> package enables us to manipulate metrics of routes a posteriori even for DHCP."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>ifmeric</literal> nous permet de manipuler a posteriori la métrique de routes même avec DHCP."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12863
msgid "The following sets the <literal>eth0</literal> interface to be preferred over the <literal>wlan0</literal> interface."
msgstr "Ce qui suit permettra de rendre l'interface <literal>eth0</literal> prioritaire sur l'interface <literal>wlan0</literal>&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12867
msgid "Install the <literal>ifmetric</literal> package."
msgstr "installer le paquet <literal>ifmetric</literal>&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12872
msgid "Add an option line with \"<literal>metric 0</literal>\" just below the \"<literal>iface eth0 inet dhcp</literal>\" line."
msgstr "ajouter l'option avec «&nbsp;<literal>metric 0</literal>&nbsp;» juste en-dessous de la ligne «&nbsp;<literal>iface eth0 inet dhcp</literal>&nbsp;»&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12877
msgid "Add an option line with \"<literal>metric 1</literal>\" just below the \"<literal>iface wlan0 inet dhcp</literal>\" line."
msgstr "ajouter une ligne d'option avec «&nbsp;<literal>metric 1</literal>&nbsp;» juste en-dessous de la ligne «&nbsp;<literal>iface wlan0 inet dhcp</literal>&nbsp;»."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12881
msgid "The metric 0 means the highest priority route and is the default one.  The larger metric value means lower priority routes. The IP address of the active interface with the lowest metric value becomes the originating one. See <literal>ifmetric</literal>(8)."
msgstr "«&nbsp;metric 0&nbsp;» indique la route de plus haute priorité et c'est celle par défaut. La plus grande valeur de «&nbsp;metric&nbsp;» indique une route de moindre priorité. L'adresse IP de l'interface active ayant la valeur de «&nbsp;metric&nbsp;» la plus basse devient celle d'origine. Voir <literal>ifmetric</literal>(8)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12884
msgid "The virtual interface"
msgstr "L'interface virtuelle"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12885
msgid "A single physical Ethernet interface can be configured as multiple virtual interfaces with different IP addresses.  Usually the purpose is to connect an interface to several IP subnetworks.  For example, IP address based virtual web hosting by a single network interface is one such application."
msgstr "Une seule interface ethernet physique peut être configurée en tant que de multiples interfaces virtuelles avec différentes adresses IP. Habituellement, le but est de connecter une interface à plusieurs sous-réseaux ayant des IP différentes. Par exemple, l'hébergement web virtuel basé sur l'IP avec une seule interface réseau est une application de ce type."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12886
msgid "For example, let's suppose the following."
msgstr "Supposons, par exemple, ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12890
msgid "A single Ethernet interface on your host is connected to a Ethernet hub (not to the broadband router)."
msgstr "une seule interface ethernet de votre machine est raccordée à un «&nbsp;hub ethernet&nbsp;» (pas au routeur à large bande)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12895
msgid "The Ethernet hub is connected to both the Internet and LAN network."
msgstr "le concentrateur ethernet est connecté à la fois à Internet et au réseau local&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12900
msgid "The LAN network uses subnet <literal>192.168.0.x/24</literal>."
msgstr "le réseau local utilise le sous-réseau <literal>192.168.0.x/24</literal>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12905
msgid "Your host uses DHCP served IP address with the physical interface <literal>eth0</literal> for the Internet."
msgstr "votre machine utilise une adresse IP fournie par DHCP avec l'interface physique <literal>eth0</literal> pour Internet&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12910
msgid "Your host uses <literal>192.168.0.1</literal> with the virtual interface <literal>eth0:0</literal> for the LAN."
msgstr "votre machine utilise <literal>192.168.0.1</literal> avec l'interface virtuelle <literal>eth0:0</literal> pour le réseau local."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12914
msgid "The following stanzas in \"<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>\" configure your network."
msgstr "Les entrées suivantes de «&nbsp;<literal>/etc/network/interfaces</literal>&nbsp;» permettent de configurer votre réseau&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12915
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
" metric 0\n"
"iface eth0:0 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.0.1\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" network 192.168.0.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.0.255\n"
" metric 1"
msgstr ""
"iface eth0 inet dhcp\n"
" metric 0\n"
"iface eth0:0 inet static\n"
" address 192.168.0.1\n"
" netmask 255.255.255.0\n"
" network 192.168.0.0\n"
" broadcast 192.168.0.255\n"
" metric 1"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12924
msgid "Although this configuration example with <ulink url=\"&networkaddresstranslationnat;\">network address translation (NAT)</ulink> using <ulink url=\"&netfilteriptables;\">netfilter/iptables</ulink> (see <xref linkend=\"_netfilter_infrastructure\"/>) can provide cheap router for the LAN with only single interface, there is no real firewall capability with such set up.  You should use 2 physical interfaces with NAT to secure the local network from the Internet."
msgstr "Bien que cet exemple de configuration avec <ulink url=\"&networkaddresstranslationnat;\">traduction d'adresse réseau (NAT)</ulink> en utilisant <ulink url=\"&netfilteriptables;\">netfilter/iptables</ulink> (voir <xref linkend=\"_netfilter_infrastructure\"/>) puisse fournir un routeur économique pour le réseau local avec une seule interface, il n'y a pas, avec votre configuration, de possibilité réelle de parefeu. Vous devriez utiliser deux interfaces physiques avec NAT afin de sécuriser le réseau local de ce qui provient d'Internet."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12928
msgid "The advanced command syntax"
msgstr "Syntaxe de commande avancée"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12929
msgid "The <literal>ifupdown</literal> package offers advanced network configuration using the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network configuration</emphasis> name and the <emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> name.  I use slightly different terminology from one used in <literal>ifup</literal>(8) and <literal>interfaces</literal>(5)."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>ifupdown</literal> fournit une configuration avancée du réseau en utilisant le nom <emphasis role=\"strong\">configuration réseau</emphasis> et le nom <emphasis role=\"strong\">interface réseau</emphasis>. J'utilise une terminologie un peu différente de celle utilisée dans <literal>ifup</literal>(8) et <literal>interfaces</literal>(5)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12931
msgid "List of terminology for network devices"
msgstr "Terminologie des périphériques réseau"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12940
msgid "manpage terminology"
msgstr "terminologie de la page de manuel"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12943
msgid "my terminology"
msgstr "ma terminologie"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><thead><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12946
msgid "examples in the following text"
msgstr "exemple dans le texte suivant&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12955
msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">physical interface</emphasis> name"
msgstr "nom de l'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interface physique</emphasis>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12957
msgid "<emphasis role=\"strong\">network interface</emphasis> name"
msgstr "nom de l'<emphasis role=\"strong\">interface réseau</emphasis>"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:12959
