#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:13771
msgid "The TCP throughput can be maximized by adjusting TCP buffer size parameters as described in \"<ulink url=\"&tcptuningguide;\">TCP Tuning Guide</ulink>\" and \"<ulink url=\"&tcptuning;\">TCP tuning</ulink>\" for the modern high-bandwidth and high-latency WAN.  So far, the current Debian default settings serve well even for my LAN connected by the fast 1G bps FTTP service."
